((3) 0 () 0 () () (u . "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <meta name=\"format-detection\" content=\"telephone=no\">\n\n  <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"/functions.js\"></script>\n\n  <meta content=\"Alexander Nabavi-Noori | Alexander Nabavi-Noori\" name=\"title\" />\n  <meta content=\"Alexander Nabavi-Noori, Ph.D. Student at Harvard University.\" name=\"description\" />\n  <meta content=\"website\" property=\"og:type\" />\n  <meta content=\"https://alexandernnoori.com/index.html\" property=\"og:url\" />\n  <meta content=\"Alexander Nabavi-Noori | Alexander Nabavi-Noori\" property=\"og:title\" />\n  <meta content=\"Alexander Nabavi-Noori, Ph.D. Student at Harvard University.\" property=\"og:description\" />\n  <meta content=\"summary_large_image\" property=\"twitter:card\" />\n  <meta content=\"@xandernn\" property=\"twitter:site\" />\n  <meta content=\"https://alexandernnoori.com/index.html\" property=\"twitter:url\" />\n  <meta content=\"Alexander Nabavi-Noori | Alexander Nabavi-Noori\" property=\"twitter:title\" />\n  <meta content=\"Alexander Nabavi-Noori, Ph.D. Student at Harvard University.\" property=\"twitter:description\" />\n\n  <link rel=\"icon\" href=\"/favicon.ico\" />\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" media=\"all\" href=\"/fonts/fonts.css\" />\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" media=\"all\" href=\"/styles.css\" />\n\n  <title>Alexander Nabavi-Noori | Alexander Nabavi-Noori</title>\n\n  <style type=\"text/css\">\n    #switcher {\n      margin-top: 12px;\n      border: 1px solid gray;\n      box-shadow: 2px 2px;\n      cursor: default;\n      text-align: center;\n      padding-top: 0.2em;\n      padding-bottom: 0.2em;\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n\n<body id=\"body\" class=\"body-text_century-supra\">\n\n  <div id=\"switcher\"><a class=\"nav-link active\" href=\"index.html\">About</a>\n<a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"research.html\">Research</a>\n<a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"experience.html\">Experience</a>\n<a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"blog.html\">Blog</a>\n<a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"contact.html\">Contact</a>\n<a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"/ANabaviNoori_CV.pdf\">CV</a>\n</div>\n\n  <div id=\"content\">\n\n    <div id=\"doc\"><div id=\"doc\"><p><topic class=\"small\">Alexan\u00ADder Nabavi-Noori</topic></p><aside><p class=\"image\"><img src=\"images/Xander_Color.jpg\"/></p></aside><p>I am a first-year Ph.D. stu\u00ADdent and Ash\u00ADford Fel\u00ADlow in Gov\u00ADern\u00ADment and Social Pol\u00ADicy at <a href=\"https://www.gov.harvard.edu/people/graduate-students/\">Har\u00ADvard Uni\u00ADver\u00ADsity,</a> and an affil\u00ADi\u00ADate of the <a href=\"https://caps.gov.harvard.edu/\">Cen\u00ADter for Amer\u00ADi\u00ADcan Polit\u00ADi\u00ADcal Stud\u00ADies.</a> My <a class=\"xref\" hyphens=\"none\" href=\"research.html\">research</a> exam\u00ADines how legal regimes build, reshape, and con\u00ADstrain Amer\u00ADi\u00ADcan polit\u00ADi\u00ADcal insti\u00ADtu\u00ADtions, par\u00ADtic\u00ADu\u00ADlarly the fed\u00ADeral bureau\u00ADcracy and Con\u00ADgress.</p><p>I came to grad\u00ADu\u00ADate study by way of law, after work\u00ADing in var\u00ADi\u00ADous roles across the fed\u00ADeral gov\u00ADern\u00ADment: in the exec\u00ADu\u00ADtive branch, on Capi\u00ADtol Hill, and in the fed\u00ADeral judi\u00ADciary.<br/>Those expe\u00ADri\u00ADences drew me to ques\u00ADtions about how insti\u00ADtu\u00ADtions actu\u00ADally work. Much of what insti\u00ADtu\u00ADtions do—and how well they do it—turns on things legal cat\u00ADe\u00ADgories do not always cap\u00ADture: the moti\u00ADva\u00ADtions and lim\u00ADi\u00ADta\u00ADtions of the peo\u00ADple inside them, the orga\u00ADni\u00ADza\u00ADtional cul\u00ADtures that form around them, and the infor\u00ADmal prac\u00ADtices through which for\u00ADmal author\u00ADity is exer\u00ADcised. To that end, I’m inter\u00ADested in the <a href=\"colophon.html#other\">human\u00ADness of the state.</a></p><p>Out\u00ADside of research, I enjoy yoga, drink\u00ADing more cof\u00ADfee than I should, and spend\u00ADing plenty of time at book\u00ADstores. I am also inter\u00ADested in typog\u00ADra\u00ADphy and design—this site being one small out\u00ADlet for those inter\u00ADests (see the <a class=\"xref\" hyphens=\"none\" href=\"colophon.html\">colophon</a>)—and am an avid fol\u00ADlower of con\u00ADsumer tech\u00ADnol\u00ADogy.</p></div></div><a id=\"links\"></a>\n    <div class=\"gap\" style=\"height:1em\"></div>\n    <ul class=\"children\"></ul>\n\n  </div>\n\n  <div id=\"toolbar\" class=\"\">\n\n    <div id=\"navtable\">\n\n      <div>\n        <a class=\"box-link\" href=\"colophon.html\"><span class=\"arrow\">←</span>&nbsp;colophon</a>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"center\">\n        <a class=\"box-link\" href=\"/\">home</a>\n      </div>\n\n      <div>\n        <a class=\"box-link\" href=\"/ANabaviNoori_CV.pdf\">curriculum vitae&nbsp;<span class=\"arrow\">→</span></a>\n      </div>\n\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n</body>\n\n</html>"))